            "body": "<p>Ok, it looks like Clojure's persistent maps implement <code>java.util.Map<\/code> but not <code>java.util.HashMap<\/code>. This means that your Java method needs to take a <code>Map&lt;Object, Object&gt;<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you need a <code>HashMap<\/code> in Java, your Java method can pass the map from Clojure into the <code>HashMap<\/code> constructor.<\/p>\n\n<p>Is this method the actual one you're using, or a simplification?<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 34388851,
            "question_id": 34388346
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/syfph.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 927500,
